{"timestamp": "2026-06-20T17:42:29.896554", "interaction_type": "generate", "model": "qwen3-coder-next", "method": "generate", "phase": "execution", "prompt": "## Investigation Goal\n\n        You are an experienced reverse engineer and binary security analyst. \n        Determine if this binary has a backdoor.\n\n        \n        If there is a backdoor, provide the specific malicious function that it comes from.\n        Explain what caused you to think that it is a malicious function, citing what it does\n        and why that goes against what the original program did.\n\n        If you decide there is a backdoor, answer with the name of the function(s) and the relative offsets of the function(s).\n        If you decide there is not a backdoor, simply put \"there is no backdoor in this program\".\n        \n\n        File type: \n        {'MACHO'}\n\n## Execution Plan\n## Cycle 1 Depth: RECONNAISSANCE: List imports, strings, exports. Identify binary purpose, compiler, and key security-related APIs. Cover as many investigation areas as possible at a surface level.\n\nEXECUTE: list_imports(offset=0, limit=100)\nEXECUTE: list_exports(offset=0, limit=50)\nEXECUTE: list_functions(offset=0, limit=200)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(offset=0, limit=50)\n\n## Progress: Loop 1, Step 3 (completed 23 steps in this loop)\n\n## Execution Results (Loop 1):\n\nstep_L1_1: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'shell', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 22] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20]\n_xmlShell @ 10009a5a8\n_xmlShellBase @ 100099720\n_xmlShellCat @ 100099928\n_xmlShellDir @ 100099818\n_xmlShellDu @ 10009a108\n_xmlShellGrep @ 10009ca78\n_xmlShellList @ 1000995b0\n_xmlShellLoad @ 100099a70\n_xmlShellPrintNode @ 10009925c\n_xmlShellPrintNodeCtxt @ 100099284\n_xmlShellPrintXPathError @ 100098fdc\n_xmlShellPrintXPathResult @ 100099378\n_xmlShellPrintXPathResultCtxt @ 1000993a0\n_xmlShellPwd @ 10009a4cc\n_xmlShellRNGValidate @ 10009c8a4\n_xm...\n\nstep_L1_2: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'backdoor', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: No functions matching 'backdoor'\n\nstep_L1_3: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'remote', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: No functions matching 'remote'\n\nstep_L1_4: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'exec', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 13] [Showing: 1-13]\n_xmlFARegExec @ 1000f050c\n_xmlFARegExecRollBack @ 1000f4ff8\n_xmlFARegExecSave @ 1000f4c60\n_xmlFARegExecSaveInputString @ 1000f48bc\n_xmlRegExecErrInfo @ 1000ee128\n_xmlRegExecGetValues @ 1000ed644\n_xmlRegExecNextValues @ 1000ed5fc\n_xmlRegExecPushString @ 1000ebfe0\n_xmlRegExecPushString2 @ 1000ed040\n_xmlRegExecPushStringInternal @ 1000ec018\n_xmlRegFreeExecCtxt @ 1000ebd90\n_xmlRegNewExecCtxt @ 1000eba4c\n_xmlRegexpExec @ 1000f04a0\n\nstep_L1_5: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'system', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 7] [Showing: 1-7]\n_htmlParseSystemLiteral @ 100093920\n_xmlACatalogResolveSystem @ 1000dd14c\n_xmlCatalogGetSGMLSystem @ 1000dd75c\n_xmlCatalogGetSystem @ 1000e0804\n_xmlCatalogResolveSystem @ 1000dfcd0\n_xmlParseSystemLiteral @ 10001eaf4\n_xmlSAX2GetSystemId @ 10017dc24\n\nstep_L1_6: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'socket', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 2] [Showing: 1-2]\n_socket @ 1001941bc\n_xmlNanoFTPGetSocket @ 1000da6b8\n\nstep_L1_7: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'connect', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 5] [Showing: 1-5]\n_connect @ 100193f4c\n_xmlNanoFTPCloseConnection @ 1000d90a0\n_xmlNanoFTPConnect @ 1000d7128\n_xmlNanoFTPConnectTo @ 1000d83ac\n_xmlNanoFTPGetConnection @ 1000d8850\n\nstep_L1_8: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'network', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: No functions matching 'network'\n\nstep_L1_9: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'tcp', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: No functions matching 'tcp'\n\nstep_L1_10: search_functions_by_name({'query': 'bind', 'offset': 0, 'limit': 20})\nResult: [Total: 4] [Showing: 1-4