{"timestamp": "2026-06-20T18:12:42.874133", "interaction_type": "generate", "model": "qwen3-coder-next", "method": "generate", "phase": "execution", "prompt": "## Investigation Goal\n\n        You are an experienced reverse engineer and binary security analyst. \n        Determine if this binary has a backdoor.\n\n        \n        If there is a backdoor, provide the specific malicious function that it comes from.\n        Explain what caused you to think that it is a malicious function, citing what it does\n        and why that goes against what the original program did.\n\n        If you decide there is a backdoor, answer with the name of the function(s) and the relative offsets of the function(s).\n        If you decide there is not a backdoor, simply put \"there is no backdoor in this program\".\n        \n\n        File type: \n        {'MACHO'}\n\n## Execution Plan\n## Cycle 1 Depth: RECONNAISSANCE: List imports, strings, exports. Identify binary purpose, compiler, and key security-related APIs. Cover as many investigation areas as possible at a surface level.\n\nEXECUTE: list_imports(offset=0, limit=50)\nEXECUTE: list_exports(offset=0, limit=50)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(offset=0, limit=30)\nEXECUTE: list_functions(offset=0, limit=50)\n\n## Progress: Loop 1, Step 2 (completed 4 steps in this loop)\n\n## Execution Results (Loop 1):\n\nstep_L1_1: list_imports({'offset': 0, 'limit': 50})\nResult: [Total: 105] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20]\n__Unwind_Resume -> EXTERNAL:00000001\nlogic_error -> EXTERNAL:00000002\nreserve -> EXTERNAL:00000003\npush_back -> EXTERNAL:00000004\nterminate -> EXTERNAL:00000005\noperator.delete -> EXTERNAL:00000006\noperator.new -> EXTERNAL:00000007\n___cxa_allocate_exception -> EXTERNAL:00000008\n___cxa_begin_catch -> EXTERNAL:00000009\n___cxa_end_catch -> EXTERNAL:0000000a\n___cxa_free_exception -> EXTERNAL:0000000b\n___cxa_throw -> EXTERNAL:0000000c\n___darwin...\n\nstep_L1_2: list_exports({'offset': 0, 'limit': 50})\nResult: [Total: 1565] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20]\n__mh_execute_header -> 100000000\nMACH_HEADER -> 100000000\nignore -> 1000019dc\n__Z6ignorePvPKcz -> 1000019dc\n_LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput -> 1000019e0\nentry -> 100001cb8\n_main -> 100001cb8\n_initxmlDefaultSAXHandler -> 100002498\n_inithtmlDefaultSAXHandler -> 100002694\n_initdocbDefaultSAXHandler -> 10000281c\n_xmlGetPredefinedEntity -> 1000029c4\n_xmlAddDtdEntity -> 100002b8c\n_xmlAddDocEntity -> 1000031a0\n_xmlNewEntity -> 100003300\n_xmlGetParameter...\n\nstep_L1_3: list_strings({'offset': 0, 'limit': 30})\nResult: [Total: 9229] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20]\n1000006b0: \"/usr/lib/libSystem.B.dylib\"\n100194328: \"/tmp/generate_temporary_file.XXXXXX\"\n10000058c: \"/usr/lib/dyld\"\n100000618: \"/usr/lib/libz.1.dylib\"\n100000648: \"/usr/lib/libiconv.2.dylib\"\n100000680: \"/usr/lib/libc++.1.dylib\"\n10019434c: \"Failed to allocate file name buffer.\"\n100194371: \"Failed to make temporary file.\"\n100194390: \"wb\"\n100194393: \"Failed to open file descriptor.\"\n1001943b3: \"Failed to write all bytes to file (%zu out of %z...\n\nstep_L1_4: list_functions({'offset': 0, 'limit': 50})\nResult: [Total: 2844] [Showing: 1-50] [Next: offset=50, limit=50]\n___clang_call_terminate at 1000020e0\nignore at 1000019dc\n_LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput at 1000019e0\nConsumeRandomLengthString at 100001bac\n~FuzzerTemporaryFile at 100001c70\nentry at 100001cb8\nshrink_to_fit[abi:ne180100] at 100001f40\nFuzzerTemporaryFile at 1000020f0\nConsumeBytes<unsigned_char> at 1000021c8\nshrink_to_fit at 1000022ac\n__throw_length_error[abi:ne180100] at 100002410\n__throw_length_error[abi:ne180100] at 100002424\nlength_error[abi:n...\n\n## Investigation Coverage\nProgress: 3/8 areas (38%)\n\n### \u274c Not Yet Investigated\n- **service_management**: Windows service registration and management\n  Search for: APIs=[CreateServiceW, OpenServiceW, OpenSCManagerW] Strings=[service, svc, boot]\n- **privilege_escalation**: Token and