{"timestamp": "2026-06-20T18:23:01.852228", "interaction_type": "generate", "model": "qwen3-coder-next", "method": "generate", "phase": "execution", "prompt": "## Investigation Goal\n\n        You are an experienced reverse engineer and binary security analyst. \n        Determine if this binary has a backdoor.\n\n        \n        If there is a backdoor, provide the specific malicious function that it comes from.\n        Explain what caused you to think that it is a malicious function, citing what it does\n        and why that goes against what the original program did.\n\n        If you decide there is a backdoor, answer with the name of the function(s) and the relative offsets of the function(s).\n        If you decide there is not a backdoor, simply put \"there is no backdoor in this program\".\n        \n\n        File type: \n        {'MACHO'}\n\n## Execution Plan\n## Cycle 2 Depth: TARGETED SEARCH: Follow up on HIGH-priority leads from cycle 1. Search for service/privilege/path/registry strings. Focus on uncovered investigation areas.\n\nEXECUTE: get_cached_result(result_id=\"step_L1_5\")\nEXECUTE: get_cached_result(result_id=\"step_L1_1\")\nEXECUTE: get_cached_result(result_id=\"step_L1_3\")\nEXECUTE: get_cached_result(result_id=\"step_L1_4\")\nEXECUTE: search_functions_by_name(query=\"system\", offset=0, limit=20)\nEXECUTE: search_functions_by_name(query=\"exec\", offset=0, limit=20)\nEXECUTE: search_functions_by_name(query=\"socket\", offset=0, limit=20)\nEXECUTE: get_function_by_address(address=\"1000011a8\")\n\n## Progress: Loop 2, Step 3 (completed 15 steps in this loop)\n\n## Results from Previous Loop(s) (available via get_cached_result):\n- step_L1_1: [Total: 105] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20] __Unwind_Resume -> EXTERNAL:00000001 logic_...\n- step_L1_2: [Total: 1565] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20] __mh_execute_header -> 100000000 MACH_HEAD...\n- step_L1_3: [Total: 9229] [Showing: 1-20] [Next: offset=20, limit=20] 1000006b0