igation hit a dead end, explain what was tried and why it failed\n    - If goal is complete, say \"INVESTIGATION COMPLETE\" with summary\n\n    {FUNCTION_CALL_BEST_PRACTICES}\n", "temperature": 0.7, "response": "REASONING: I've completed reconnaissance and found network-related functions (FTP operations), but no obvious backdoor indicators yet. The binary appears to be libxml2 (based on function naming and XML-related imports). I need to dig deeper into suspicious patterns:\n\n1. Found a \"hidden\" string at 0x10019a164 \u2014 this is worth investigating as it could indicate hidden/backdoor functionality\n2. Network APIs are present but all seem related to FTP (xmlNanoFTP* functions), which is legitimate for an XML library\n3. No direct process creation or system() calls found in decompiled functions yet\n\nI'll search for more backdoor-related strings and examine the \"hidden\" string context. Then I'll look for less obvious indicators like suspicious data sections, obfuscated code, or hidden entry points.\n\nEXECUTE: get_xrefs_to(address=\"10019a164\", offset=0, limit=20)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"hidden\", offset=0, limit=5)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"back\", offset=0, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"debug\", offset=0, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"log\", offset=0, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"port\", offset=0, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"key\", offset=0, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_strings(filter=\"key\", offset=10, limit=10)\nEXECUTE: list_functions(offset=0, limit=50)", "response_length": 1302, "tokens": {"prompt_eval_count": 9128, "eval_count": 340, "total_count": 9468}, "timing": {"total_duration_seconds": 75.32082414627075, "total_duration_ms": 72971.130997, "load_duration_ms": 30968.738508, "prompt_eval_duration_ms": 24216.876966, "eval_duration_ms": 17644.724483}, "status": "success"}
